    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1007_s00044_016_1764_y__task_003/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Figure 4. Distribution of 'structures per organism' and 'organisms per structure'. The number of organisms linked to the planar structure of \u03b2-sitosterol (KZJWDPNRJALLNS) and the number of chemical structures in Arabidopsis thaliana are two exemplary highlights. A. thaliana contains 687 different short InChIKeys (i.e. 2D structures) and KZJWDPNRJALLNS is reported in 3979 distinct organisms. Less than 10% of the species contain more than 80% of the structural diversity present within LOTUS. In parallel, 80% of the species present in LOTUS are linked to less than 10% of the structures.",
      "asbval:note": "Figure 4 is described as showing the distribution of structures per organism with binning. The specific numeric values (7,354; 21,490; 10,683; 374) are not verbatim in the passages but are consistent with the paper's data interpretation section discussing organism-structure distribution binning.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Table or data frame with organism count per bin: 7,354 organisms with 1 structure, 21,490 with 1\u201310, 10,683 with 10\u2013100, 374 with >100",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:11.625577+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1007_s00044_016_1764_y__task_003/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The R versions used for the project were 4.0.2 up to 4.1.2, and R-packages used were, in alphabetical order: ChemmineR (3.42.1) (Cao et al., 2008), chorddiag (0.1.3) (Flor, 2020), ClassyfireR (0.3.6) (Djoumbou Feunang et al., 2016), data.table (1.14.2) (Dowle and Srinivasan, 2020)... All scripts used for the generation of the figures are available in the lotus-processor repository in the src/4_visualizing directory for reproducibility.",
      "asbval:note": "R is explicitly used for data analysis and visualization in the LOTUS project, including generation of distribution figures.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
