    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/categorical-grouping-and-aggregation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The alluvial plot in Figure 2 illustrates the individual contribution of each source and original subcategory that led to the processed categories: structure, organism, and reference... The figure highlights, for example, the essential contribution of the reference DOI category to the final validated entries.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper performs extensive grouping and aggregation of structures, organisms, and references by categorical attributes (source, subcategory, validation status) to summarize distributions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "categorical-grouping-and-aggregation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Group entities (organisms, structures, or references) by a discrete categorical attribute and count or aggregate members within each group to summarize distributions and validate against reference benchmarks.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:34:50.462480+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/categorical-grouping-and-aggregation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To illustrate the nature and dimensions of the LOTUS dataset, some selected examples of data interpretation are shown. First, the distribution of chemical structures among four important NP reservoirs: plants, fungi, animals, and bacteria (Table 3). Then, the distribution of biological organisms according to the number of related chemical structures and likewise the distribution of chemical structures across biological organisms are illustrated (Figure 4).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly uses grouping and aggregation to validate and characterize the composition of the structure-organism pair collection.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "categorical-grouping-and-aggregation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill is essential for validating curated datasets against published counts and understanding the composition of large structure-organism pair collections.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:34:50.462480+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/categorical-grouping-and-aggregation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Readily achievable outcomes from LOTUS show that the depth of exploration of the world of NP is rather limited: as depicted in Figure 4, on average, three organisms are reported per chemical structure and eleven structures per organism. Notably, half of all structures have been reported from a single organism and half of all studied organisms are reported to contain five or fewer structures.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates binning organisms and structures by count ranges (single organism, five or fewer structures, etc.) to characterize distribution.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "categorical-grouping-and-aggregation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have a flat table of structure-organism pairs or entity records and need to summarize their distribution across categorical bins (e.g., organism counts binned by number of associated structures in categories: 1, 1\u201310, 10\u2013100, >100).",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:34:50.462480+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/categorical-grouping-and-aggregation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The R versions used for the project were 4.0.2 up to 4.1.2, and R-packages used were, in alphabetical order: ChemmineR (3.42.1)... data.table (1.14.2)... tidyverse (1.3.1)... All scripts used for the generation of the figures are available in the lotus-processor repository in the src/4_visualizing directory for reproducibility.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses R with tidyverse (which includes dplyr) and data.table for grouping and aggregation operations.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "categorical-grouping-and-aggregation",
