      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:35:29.653719+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chemical-structure-sanitization-and-validation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "InChI were translated to SMILES using the RDKit, 2021 implementation in Python 3.8 (src/2_curating/2_editing/structure/1_translating/inchi.py)... The Python version used was 3.7.12 up to 3.9.7, and the Python packages utilized were, in alphabetical order: ... rdkit (2021.09.2) (RDKit, 2021), scipy (1.7.3) (Virtanen et al., 2020)...",
      "asbval:note": "Python is confirmed as the execution environment for chemical structure processing. However, the specific file paths 'sanitizing.py' and 'smiles.py' are not explicitly named in the passages. The paper references src/2_curating/2_editing/structure/ directory but does not list individual Python script filenames for sanitization.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chemical-structure-sanitization-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Python as a tool with evidence_spans referencing sanitizing.py and smiles.py",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:35:29.653719+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chemical-structure-sanitization-and-validation/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To retrieve as much information as possible from the original structure field(s) of each of the sources, the following procedure was followed... If no structural identifier was available, the nominal identifier was translated to InChI first thanks to OPSIN... Before the translation process, some typical chemical structure-related greek characters (such as \u03b1, \u00df) were replaced by their textual equivalents (alpha, beta) to obtain better results... The chemical sanitization step sought to standardize the representation of chemical structures coming from different sources. It consisted of three main stages (standardizing, fragment removal, and uncharging)... After this re-ranking step, only the first candidate was kept... After deduplication, 2M+ unique structure-organism pairs were obtained.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes the exact workflow: translation of chemical structures, sanitization to remove defects, and deduplication before integration with organism and reference data. This matches the scope description.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chemical-structure-sanitization-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have translated or raw SMILES strings from a chemical structure curation pipeline and need to remove invalid chemical structures, resolve sanitization errors, and eliminate redundant entries before integration with organism and reference metadata.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:35:29.653719+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/count-verification-against-published-values/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "At its current stage of development, LOTUS disseminates 750,000+ referenced structure-organism pairs. These efforts and experiences represent an intensive preliminary curatorial phase and the first major step towards providing a high-quality, computer-interpretable knowledge base... In total, 163,800 structures with fully defined stereochemistry were uploaded as \"chemical compounds\" (Q11173), and 106,669 structures without fully defined stereochemistry were uploaded as \"group of stereoisomers\" (Q59199015)... In the end, the disseminated data contained 290,000+ unique chemical structures, 40,000+ distinct organisms and 75,000+ references.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly reports headline statistics (750,000+ pairs, 290,000+ structures, 40,000+ organisms, 75,000+ references) and provides frozen datasets with 2D/3D stratification (163,800 with full stereochemistry, 106,669 without), enabling independent verification.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "count-verification-against-published-values",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Independently reproduce and verify aggregate counts of key entities (structure-organism pairs, unique structures, organisms, source databases) from a published natural products dataset by loading curated data files, deduplicating on identifier columns, and comparing results again",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:35:49.474021+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/count-verification-against-published-values/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The R versions used for the project were 4.0.2 up to 4.1.2, and R-packages used were, in alphabetical order: ... data.table (1.14.2) ... tidyverse (1.3.1) (Wickham et al., 2019)... All scripts used for the generation of the figures are available in the lotus-processor repository in the src/4_visualizing directory for reproducibility.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms R usage with data.table and tidyverse (which includes dplyr) for data processing and analysis. Scripts are available in lotus-processor repository.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "count-verification-against-published-values",
