      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "All scripts used for the generation of the figures are available in the lotus-processor repository in the src/4_visualizing directory for reproducibility... The R versions used for the project were 4.0.2 up to 4.1.2, and R-packages used were, in alphabetical order: ... data.table (1.14.2) ... tidyverse (1.3.1)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms use of R with data.table and tidyverse (dplyr) for aggregation operations, but does not explicitly name the specific functions (group_by, n_distinct). The tools and their typical usage patterns are confirmed, but exact function names are not verbatim in passages.",
