    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/database-metadata-enumeration/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "[SUBSTRING-MATCH for lotus-processor | role: data processing] The source data curation system is available at https://github.com/lotusnprod/lotus-processor (copy archived at swh:1:rev:78e6065d8eb9d0b0d11c2ea8de6ac66b445bca0e, Rutz, 2022a). This program takes the source data as input and outputs curated data, ready for dissemination. The first step involves checking if the source data has already been processed. If not, all three elements (biological organism, chemical structures, and references) are submitted to various steps of translation and curation, before validation for dissemination.",
      "asbval:note": "lotus-processor is the primary orchestration tool for LOTUS data harmonization, processing, and validation\u2014all steps that precede enumeration and verification.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "database-metadata-enumeration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "lotus-processor with role: Reference implementation and workflow orchestration for LOTUS dataset processing; includes standardization, cleaning, and integration steps that precede enumeration.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:54.741129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/database-metadata-enumeration/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After deduplication, 2M+ unique structure-organism pairs were obtained. After the curation of all three objects, all of them were put together again... Only entries containing a structure, an organism, and a reference after curation were kept.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates that enumeration requires pair-level data and that aggregation/deduplication affects counts, supporting the scope limitation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "database-metadata-enumeration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "If the input data is already aggregated or summarized (i.e., not at the raw structure-organism pair row level), direct enumeration will not work",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:54.741129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/database-metadata-enumeration/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "As data formats are largely inhomogeneous among existing electronic NP resources, fields related to chemical structure, biological organism and references are variable and essentially not standardized. Therefore, LOTUS implements multiple stages of harmonization, processing, and validation (Figure 1, stages 1\u20133).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly documents heterogeneous source database encoding and the need for standardization, supporting the scope limitation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "database-metadata-enumeration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "If source database attribution is missing or encoded in a non-standardized way in your dataset version, enumeration of source databases may be incomplete or unreliable.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:54.741129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/database-metadata-enumeration/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In total, 163,800 structures with fully defined stereochemistry were uploaded as 'chemical compounds' (Q11173), and 106,669 structures without fully defined stereochemistry were uploaded as 'group of stereoisomers' (Q59199015).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper distinguishes between 2D and stereochemistry-defined structures, demonstrating that enumeration granularity matters for verification.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "database-metadata-enumeration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "If you only have 2D structures but the reported statistic separates 3D and 2D counts, you cannot independently verify",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:36:54.741129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dataset-integrity-assessment/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "An entry was considered as valid if: (i) the structure (in the form of any structural descriptor that could be linked to the final sanitized InChIKey) was described in the reference (ii) the containing organism (as any organism descriptor that could be linked to the accepted canonical name) was described in the reference and (iii) the reference was describing the occurrence of the chemical structure in the biological organism... The resulting data is also available in the dataset shared at https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794106 (Rutz et al., 2021a)... At the time of writing (2021-12-20), this query (without the LIMIT 1000) returned 951,800 entries; a frozen query result is available at https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5668854 (Rutz et al., 2021d).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes validation of structure-organism pairs and provides frozen datasets with documented counts (750,000+ pairs, 290,000+ structures, 40,000+ organisms, 75,000+ references). The task of reproducing and verifying these statistics is directly aligned with the paper's curation and validation workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-7554-elife-70780",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dataset-integrity-assessment",
