    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/organism-count-distribution-analysis/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "as depicted in Figure 4, on average, three organisms are reported per chemical structure and eleven structures per organism. Notably, half of all structures have been reported from a single organism and half of all studied organisms are reported to contain five or fewer structures.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper reports organism-structure distribution analysis but does NOT explicitly partition into four bins. Instead, it reports: (1) half of organisms have \u22645 structures, (2) half of structures from single organism, (3) average 11 structures per organism. The binning scheme (1, 1\u201310, 10\u2013100, >100) claimed in the card is not present in the paper. The paper performs distribution analysis but with different categorical boundaries.",
