      "asbval:evidence_quote": "At its current stage of development, LOTUS disseminates 750,000+ referenced structure-organism pairs. ... In total, 163,800 structures with fully defined stereochemistry were uploaded as 'chemical compounds' (Q11173), and 106,669 structures without fully defined stereochemistry were uploaded as 'group of stereoisomers' (Q59199015).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper reports 750,000+ referenced structure-organism pairs total, not 484,174. The card's specific numbers (484,174 pairs, 42,166 organisms) do not appear in the passages. The paper does mention 290,000+ unique chemical structures and 40,000+ distinct organisms, but these are different metrics than the card claims.",
